00:00:08.310 --> 00:00:10.450
And we looked last time at the
Boltzmann factor,

00:00:10.450 --> 00:00:15.600
that e^-H/RT^( )or
ΔH/RT,

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:19.597
which tells you the temperature
dependence of the equilibrium

00:00:19.597 --> 00:00:20.330
constant.
 

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:21.780
It gives you the equilibrium
constant;

00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:26.246
remember at room temperatures
3/4thsΔH in

00:00:26.246 --> 00:00:27.341
kilocalories.
 

00:00:27.341 --> 00:00:28.100
Right?
 

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:32.152
And we saw last time that that
comes from counting arrangements

00:00:32.152 --> 00:00:34.440
of a fixed number of energy
bits.

00:00:34.440 --> 00:00:37.654
And the important thing is that
they're random,

00:00:37.654 --> 00:00:40.310
