likely.

00:00:40.310 --> 00:00:43.550
&lt;&lt;Technical
adjustment&gt;&gt;

00:00:43.550 --> 00:00:46.567
That has interesting
philosophical implications I

00:00:46.567 --> 00:00:47.070
think.
 

00:00:47.070 --> 00:00:51.613
Do you remember at the start of
the course we were talking about

00:00:51.613 --> 00:00:53.920
types of authority,
and in particular,

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:55.981
remember, in Hamlet,
Act V, Scene II,

00:00:55.981 --> 00:00:59.526
he says, "There's a
divinity that shapes our

00:00:59.526 --> 00:01:00.560
ends."
 

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:04.120
So this was a traditional view
in society.

00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:08.530
But then this guy came along,
in 1859.

00:01:08.530 --> 00:01:10.659
Do you know who that is?
 

00:01:10.659 --> 00:01:12.659
Charles Darwin,
with The Origin of the

00:01:12.659 --> 00:01:13.360
Species.
 

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:17.168
So there was conflict between
the religious fundamentalists

00:01:17.168 --> 00:01:20.060
and Darwinists that continues to
this day.

00:01:20.060 --> 00:01:23.644
But I think they really miss
the point, because Darwin had

00:01:23.644 --> 00:01:27.040
the idea that things were
developing and getting better

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:27.858
all the time.
 

00:01:27.858 --> 00:01:28.549
Right?
 

00:01:28.549 --> 00:01:32.016
So there's a certain
compatibility between that and

00:01:32.016 --> 00:01:35.000
the sensibilities of the
fundamentalists.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:38.952
But also, not too long from
then, this guy came along,

00:01:38.952 --> 00:01:42.681
Boltzmann, and he said
everything is driven just by

00:01:42.681 --> 00:01:43.800
randomness.
 

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:46.140
There's no goal for everything.
 

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:48.842
That should be the real
conflict, between religious

00:01:48.842 --> 00:01:51.220
fundamentalists and science,
is Boltzmann.

00:01:51.220 --> 00:01:55.101
But so few people understand
what Boltzmann did that there's

00:01:55.101 --> 00:01:57.010
no reason for the conflict.
 

00:01:57.010 --> 00:01:59.364
At any rate,
we saw where the Boltzmann

00:01:59.364 --> 00:02:02.030
factor came from,
in terms of statistics.

00:02:02.030 --> 00:02:05.659
Then there's the entropy
factor, which we saw last time.

00:02:05.659 --> 00:02:08.000
And notice that,
as I've written it here,

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:10.516
in the top equation,
the one with Boltzmann,

00:02:10.516 --> 00:02:13.502
there's an R,
and the one at the bottom has a

00:02:13.502 --> 00:02:14.378
k.
 

00:02:14.378 --> 00:02:17.240
Sometimes you see R's
and sometimes see k's.

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:19.090
They're actually the same thing.
 

00:02:19.090 --> 00:02:23.217
The k is if you measure
the energy per molecule,

00:02:23.217 --> 00:02:27.270
and R is if you measure
the energy per mole.

00:02:27.270 --> 00:02:30.522
So all you have is Avogadro's
number is included in one of

00:02:30.522 --> 00:02:31.949
them and not the other.
 

00:02:31.949 --> 00:02:34.538
They're really the same thing,
these two exponentials.

00:02:34.538 --> 00:02:38.652
But at any rate,
we can cancel the T's

00:02:38.652 --> 00:02:43.045
and know that that
e^S/k^( )is a counting

00:02:43.045 --> 00:02:46.305
number, W;
the number of molecular

00:02:46.305 --> 00:02:47.770
structures being grouped.
 

00:02:47.770 --> 00:02:51.366
And we saw that at the end of
last time in terms of gauche-

00:02:51.366 --> 00:02:52.669
versus anti-butane.
 

00:02:52.669 --> 00:02:57.131
And remember that S = ln
k -- which is the same

00:02:57.131 --> 00:03:02.520
equation, just the log on each
side -- is on Boltzmann's tomb.

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:07.020
But let's look at one more
example, in terms of

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:08.389
cyclohexane.
 

00:03:08.389 --> 00:03:13.284
Do you remember the cyclohexane
conorformers --

00:03:13.284 --> 00:03:17.330
&lt;&lt;technical
adjustment&gt;&gt;

00:03:17.330 --> 00:03:21.632
-- remember the cyclohexane
conformers, if it's a chair,

00:03:21.632 --> 00:03:23.038
it's very rigid.
 

00:03:23.038 --> 00:03:23.907
Why is it rigid?
 

00:03:23.907 --> 00:03:24.830
Do you remember?
 

00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:28.250
Why is it hard to twist?
 

00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:33.789
With respect to the molecular
model, why is it hard to twist?

00:03:33.789 --> 00:03:36.699
Eric?
 

00:03:36.699 --> 00:03:40.758
Why does this particular model,
in which rotation around bonds

00:03:40.758 --> 00:03:44.018
is completely free,
why is it hard to rotate to go

00:03:44.018 --> 00:03:44.949
like this?
 

00:03:44.949 --> 00:03:46.919
Why is there a click?
 

